  "prompt": "I have a very old account in central bank in which no mobile number is registered. How to register my mobile number now?",
  "response": "To register your mobile number with a central bank account, the process can vary depending on the specific bank and country regulations. However, here are general steps you can follow:\n\n1. **Visit the Bank**: The most straightforward way is to visit the nearest branch of the bank where you hold the account. Bring valid identification and any account documentation you have.\n\n2. **Check Online Options**: Some banks allow customers to update their mobile numbers through online banking. Log in to your account on the bank\u2019s official website to see if this option is available.\n\n3. **Call Customer Service**: Contact the bank's customer service or helpline. They can provide specific instructions on how to register your mobile number. Make sure to have your account details handy for verification.\n\n4. **Submit a Request**: Some banks may require you to fill out a form or submit a request letter to register your mobile number. Inquire about any such procedures when you visit or call.\n\n5. **Authentication**: Be prepared to answer security questions or provide identity verification documents to ensure that you are the legitimate account holder.\n\n6. **Follow Up**: After submitting your request, check back with the bank to ensure that your mobile number has been successfully updated.\n\nAlways ensure you are using official bank communication channels to avoid falling victim to fraud.",
